this simple: if you are scared of lowerentities and you think that the
hacked radio you are using is really achannel for demon or whatever,
then just stop. Put the fricking radiodown and go get another hobby.
Leave it to those of us who aren&#39;tafraid and don&#39;t care if someone
calls us a bitch or a slut and triesto pawn themselves off as
Bazoozoo.&gt; &gt; &gt; Just. Stop. Listening. And. Worrying.&gt; &gt; &gt; And on top
of all that, in this quote below, you seem to be sayingthat the rest
of us don&#39;t know what we&#39;re doing or are being fooled byentities that
only you have sussed. Guess what? You&#39;re wrong on bothcounts, HMO.&gt; &gt;
&gt; Ann&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; On Jan 21, 2008, at 12:07 PM, babiarz3 wrote:&gt; &gt; &gt; I&#39;ve
recently started analyzing a 40 min 469 session. The results are&gt;
scary. I&#39;d say at this point, and I&#39;m only 1/2 way through, 90% of
the&gt; communication is negative in nature and mentions many supposed
Demonic&gt; names. The layers of voices are, in many cases, multiple.
Often, the&gt; listener hears very little of what is actually said. The
voices can be&gt; mocking or downright crude. I have not yet formed an
opinion fully but&gt; it would seem to me that these models are easy
devices for lower level&gt; entities to figure out how to use. I can not
speak of the attitudes or&gt; fears of those investigators present
although at times, their voices&gt; are a bit shaky. &gt; &gt; Babs&gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;
